# Lucifer plumbing rules.
#
# Loaded by the stock Inferno plumber (/dis/plumber.dis), started from
# /lib/lucifer/boot.sh.  Every picker path — the ftree file tree, the
# context panel, an agent, or the `plumb` command — sends a file-open
# message here; the plumber forwards it to the 'presentation' port, which
# the Lucifer presentation manager (lucipres) consumes and turns into the
# right artifact: pdf/image/markdown render as content, anything else
# opens in the editor.
#
# One rule, on purpose: the presentation manager picks the renderer by
# file type, so the rules stay trivial and every file lands in the
# presentation view rather than spawning a standalone acme/charon window.
#
# to update: cat /lib/lucifer/plumbing > /chan/plumb.rules
# to read:   cat /chan/plumb.rules

# Existing files (any type, spaces allowed) go to the presentation view.
kind is text
data matches '[a-zA-Z¡-￿0-9_\-./ ]+'
data isfile	$0
data set	$file
plumb to presentation
